{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"546b","heading":"Seng Mountain and Bear Creek Scenic Areas, Jefferson National Forest, Virginia","label":"546b Seng Mountain and Bear Creek Scenic Areas, Jefferson National Forest, Virginia","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch2/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThis subtitle, referred to in subsec. (c)(1)(A), is subtitle B (§§ 1101–1107) of title I of , , , which enacted this section and , enacted provisions set out as a note below, and enacted and amended provisions listed in a table of Wilderness Areas set out under . For complete classification of subtitle B to the Code, see Tables.Pub. L. 111–11123 Stat. 1002section 546b–1 of this titlesection 1132 of this titleMar. 30, 2009","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Definitions, , , provided that:Pub. L. 111–11, title I, § 1101123 Stat. 1002Mar. 30, 2009“In this subtitle [subtitle B (§§ 1101–1107) of title I of , enacting this section and and enacting and amending provisions listed in a table of Wilderness Areas set out under ]:Pub. L. 111–11section 546b–1 of this titlesection 1132 of this title“(1).—Scenic areasThe term ‘scenic areas’ means the Seng Mountain National Scenic Area and the Bear Creek National Scenic Area.“(2).—SecretaryThe term ‘Secretary’ means the Secretary of Agriculture.”"],"amendments":["References in TextThis subtitle, referred to in subsec. (c)(1)(A), is subtitle B (§§ 1101–1107) of title I of , , , which enacted this section and , enacted provisions set out as a note below, and enacted and amended provisions listed in a table of Wilderness Areas set out under . For complete classification of subtitle B to the Code, see Tables.Pub. L. 111–11123 Stat. 1002section 546b–1 of this titlesection 1132 of this titleMar. 30, 2009","Definitions, , , provided that:Pub. L. 111–11, title I, § 1101123 Stat. 1002Mar. 30, 2009“In this subtitle [subtitle B (§§ 1101–1107) of title I of , enacting this section and and enacting and amending provisions listed in a table of Wilderness Areas set out under ]:Pub. L. 111–11section 546b–1 of this titlesection 1132 of this title“(1).—Scenic areasThe term ‘scenic areas’ means the Seng Mountain National Scenic Area and the Bear Creek National Scenic Area.“(2).—SecretaryThe term ‘Secretary’ means the Secretary of Agriculture.”"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Establishment","label":"a Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"certain National Forest System land in the Jefferson National Forest, comprising approximately 5,192 acres, as generally depicted on the map entitled “Seng Mountain and Raccoon Branch” and dated , which shall be known as the “Seng Mountain National Scenic Area”; andApril 28, 2008","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"certain National Forest System land in the Jefferson National Forest, comprising approximately 5,128 acres, as generally depicted on the map entitled “Bear Creek” and dated , which shall be known as the “Bear Creek National Scenic Area”.April 28, 2008","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Purposes","label":"b Purposes","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to ensure the protection and preservation of scenic quality, water quality, natural characteristics, and water resources of the scenic areas;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"consistent with paragraph (1), to protect wildlife and fish habitat in the scenic areas;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to protect areas in the scenic areas that may develop characteristics of old-growth forests; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"consistent with paragraphs (1), (2), and (3), to provide a variety of recreation opportunities in the scenic areas.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Administration","label":"c Administration","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"this subtitle; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the laws (including regulations) generally applicable to the National Forest System.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Authorized uses","label":"2 Authorized uses","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall only allow uses of the scenic areas that the Secretary determines will further the purposes of the scenic areas, as described in subsection (b).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Management plan","label":"d Management plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 2 years after , the Secretary shall develop as an amendment to the land and resource management plan for the Jefferson National Forest a management plan for the scenic areas.March 30, 2009","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Effect","label":"2 Effect","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Nothing in this subsection requires the Secretary to revise the land and resource management plan for the Jefferson National Forest under .section 1604 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Roads","label":"e Roads","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), after , no roads shall be established or constructed within the scenic areas.March 30, 2009","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Limitation","label":"2 Limitation","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Nothing in this subsection denies any owner of private land (or an interest in private land) that is located in a scenic area the right to access the private land.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Timber harvest","label":"f Timber harvest","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in paragraphs (2) and (3), no harvesting of timber shall be allowed within the scenic areas.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Exceptions","label":"2 Exceptions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"control fire;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide for public safety or trail access; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"control insect and disease outbreaks.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Firewood for personal use","label":"3 Firewood for personal use","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Ff%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Firewood may be harvested for personal use along perimeter roads in the scenic areas, subject to any conditions that the Secretary may impose.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Insect and disease outbreaks","label":"g Insect and disease outbreaks","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fg%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to maintain scenic quality;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to prevent tree mortality;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fg%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to reduce hazards to visitors; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fg%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to protect private land.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":"Vegetation management","label":"h Vegetation management","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may engage in vegetation manipulation practices in the scenic areas to maintain the visual quality and wildlife clearings in existence on .March 30, 2009","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"i","heading":"Motorized vehicles","label":"i Motorized vehicles","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), motorized vehicles shall not be allowed within the scenic areas.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Exceptions","label":"2 Exceptions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to carry out administrative activities that further the purposes of the scenic areas, as described in subsection (b);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to assist wildlife management projects in existence on ; andMarch 30, 2009","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F2%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"on Forest Development Roads 49410 and 84b; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/i/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fi%2F2%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"on the portion of Forest Development Road 6261 designated on the map described in subsection (a)(2) as “open seasonally”.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"j","heading":"Wildfire suppression","label":"j Wildfire suppression","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/j","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fj","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/j/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/j","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fj%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in a manner consistent with the purposes of the scenic areas, as described in subsection (b); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/j/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/j","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fj%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"using such means as the Secretary determines to be appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"k","heading":"Water","label":"k Water","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/k","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fk","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall administer the scenic areas in a manner that maintains and enhances water quality.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"l","heading":"Withdrawal","label":"l Withdrawal","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/l","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fl","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/l/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fl%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"location, entry, and patent under the mining laws; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/l/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s546b/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs546b%2Fl%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"operation of the mineral leasing and geothermal leasing laws.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
